	  Now stored in UTF-8 encoding. Japanese  users who have set
	  $unicode_encoding to 0 will need to convert their  databases to
	  UTF-8.

2005-03-29  John Beranek <jberanek@users.sourceforge.net>

	* web/: add.php (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4,
	  mrbs-1_2_3), admin.php (tags: mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4,
	  mrbs-1_2_3), auth_config.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5,
	  mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), auth_db.inc, auth_ext.inc (tags:
	  mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), auth_imap.inc
	  (tags: mrbs-1_2_3), auth_ldap.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_3),
	  auth_nis.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4,
	  mrbs-1_2_3), auth_none.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5,
	  mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), auth_nw.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6,
	  mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), auth_pop3.inc (tags:
	  mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), del.php (tags:
	  mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), del_entry.php
	  (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3),
	  edit_area_room.php (tags: mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3),
	  edit_entry.php (tags: mrbs-1_2_3), edit_entry_handler.php,
	  edit_users.php, mrbs_auth.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5,
	  mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), session_cookie.inc, session_host.inc
	  (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3),
	  session_ip.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4,
	  mrbs-1_2_3), session_nt.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6, mrbs-1_2_5,
	  mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), session_omni.inc (tags: mrbs-1_2_6,
	  mrbs-1_2_5, mrbs-1_2_4, mrbs-1_2_3), session_php.inc
	  (mrbs-1_2-branch.[1,1,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,1,1,1,2,2,1,1,1,1,1,1,1,1])
	  (utags: mrbs-1_2-branch_lastmerge, mrbs-1_2_2): * Made username
	  matching case insensitive throughout. Auth schemes  may still
	  have case sensitive usernames though.

	  * auth_config username matching made case insensitive.

	  * Improved auth system, the session code doesn't need to return
	  the user password any more, and getAuthorised() now only requires
	   one parameter.

	  * session_cookie.inc now deletes the cookie when the user logs
	  out.	 User password isn't stored in a cookie any more, which is
	  much more   secure.

	  * session_php.inc now creates a session for the directory MRBS is
	   run from, instead of assuming '/'. Additionally, session data is
	   deleted on log out, and the user's password isn't stored in the
	  session data any more.

