	  month.

2004-04-11  Thierry Bothorel <thierry_bo@users.sourceforge.net>

	* web/: auth_db.inc (1.3), lang.en (1.21), lang.fr (1.20),
	  report.php (1.19), session_cookie.inc (1.7), session_php.inc
	  (1.7): + If auth_db is used with session_cookie or session_php,
	  the message "you are XXXX" becomes a link to all upcoming entries
	  belonging to XXXX (report page). If auth_db is not used, the
	  previous empty HREF link "you are XXXX" is useless and is now a
	  simple text message.

